reviews.review: Though I liked it very much, my biggest disappointment was Harrison Ford was not listed in the credits.
JJ Abrahams ruined the ending to the saga.
Didn’t close all the loops, but a good ending.

The Rise of Skywalker was in my opinion an overall good movie. 
It did have a some downfalls, and a few plotholes, one of which was pretty annoying, hence why i'm only giving it 4 stars. 
Contrary to what i've heard several people say, i did not find it to be messy at all, albeit maybe a tiny bit too fast paced, however there was a clear goal throughout the movie that they constantly moved towards. There were a few new character introductions that i would've rather been without, considering this is the last movie, but luckily most of these characters were relatively irrelevant. It made me laugh, cry, and had me in suspense, and i never felt like it got dragged out or got boring. 

Overall i feel like it did a good job of tying the ends together, especially considering that it had to work around TLJ, which in my opinion with no doubt was the worst of the new 3, and despite the flaws, i enjoyed it all the way through.
Not very sympathetic characters.  Same old thing.  One big noisy chase/fight. Will make a bumpy Disneyland ride.

La califico alto por varias cosas; es el cierre de la saga de los Skywalker, retoman mucho de lo que les había faltado retormar en los 2 episiodios anteriores, desarrollan algunos personajes secundarios muy meriotorios (i.e. Poe), hay un claro hilo que conduce a un cierre emocional y emocionante, las secuencias de batalla son ESTUPENDAS.

Creo que había cosas que podrían haberse hecho mejor, como el desarrollo de los personajes de Kylo Ren y Rey, especialmente en ese supuesto vínculo que la fuerza les da, en los tres episodios como que eso nunca encajó y este no fue la excepción. Yo por ejemplo hubiera desarrollado mucho más la química entre Finn y Rey y hubiera hecho crecer en villanía a Kylo Ren, pero bueno no se puede todo.

Es un 'must' seas o no fan de la saga pues es el fin de una época.
Super cool. Love how they tied everything together.
Great wrap up to the saga!  Full of emotion & surprises!  I loved how it all ended!
